author: app.com
title: Holmdel picks up 1st win of 2015 season over Pinelands
text:
MORE HOLMDEL - The Hornets of Holmdel came away with an impressive 34-3 victory against Pinelands Regional for their first win of the season on Homecoming night Friday.
Holmdel (1-5) made a statement right away as they found the end zone on their third play from scrimmage. Junior quarterback Aneesh Agrawal completed a 48 yard pass to senior wide receiver William Van Name to give the Hornets a 7-0 lead. On their next drive, Agrawal converted on fourth-and-five by rushing for 23 yards which set up a two yard touchdown run by senior Matthew Nuzzi to extend the advantage to 13-0.
Pinelands (0-7) got on the board in the second quarter as AJ Long kicked a 27-yard field goal, but Holmdel responded with another touchdown, this one a two yard run by senior Adnan Bashir to make it 20-3, which was the score into halftime.
